💳 Data Protection Techniques

Tokenization

Replaces sensitive data (e.g., credit card numbers) with non-sensitive tokens

Actual sensitive data stored securely outside the transaction system

Reduces breach exposure and PCI scope

Vendor Diversity

Using multiple vendors for similar services

Reduces systemic risk from a single zero-day vulnerability

Prevents single point of failure

📊 Application Logging

Application logs track:

User transactions

Actions taken

Error events

Critical for:

Incident response

Fraud detection

Forensic investigations

📦 Containerization Security

Containers:

Package only necessary components and dependencies

Reduce OS footprint

Minimize required patches

Improve isolation

Faster deployment and simpler update management compared to full OS environments

